HEADWORD: Myall wood
<hw>My*all" wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A durable,
fragrant, and dark-colored Australian wood, used by the natives for
spears. It is obtained from the small tree <spn>Acacia
homolophylla</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Myaria</ent>⟦br⟧
